title: Gun salutes commemorate the Queen's Sapphire Jubilee
text: show ad Congratulations ma'am! Gun salutes ring out across London to commemorate the Queen becoming the first British monarch to celebrate a Sapphire Jubilee Today marks 65 years since the Queen acceded to the throne in 1952 following the death of her father To commemorate her sapphire jubilee gun salutes were sounded in London and elsewhere in the country The Queen spent her jubilee privately at her Sandringham Estate in Norfolk Published: 16:25 GMT, 6 February 2017 | Updated: 19:22 GMT, 6 February 2017 176 shares
